usdDvmrpMIB.name: usdDvmrpMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

usdDvmrpMIB.contactinfo: Unisphere Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdDvmrpMIB.description: The Enterprise MIB module for management of Unisphere DVMRP routers.

usdDvmrpAdminState.name: usdDvmrpAdminState
usdDvmrpAdminState.description: Controls whether usdDvmrp is enabled or not.

usdDvmrpMcastAdminState.name: usdDvmrpMcastAdminState
usdDvmrpMcastAdminState.description: Whether Multicast is enabled or not. This is settable via the multicast component.

usdDvmrpRouteHogNotification.name: usdDvmrpRouteHogNotification
usdDvmrpRouteHogNotification.description: The number of routes allowed within a 1 minute interval before a trap is issued warning that there may be a route surge going on.

usdDvmrpRouteLimit.name: usdDvmrpRouteLimit
usdDvmrpRouteLimit.description: The limit on the number of routes that may be advertised on a usdDvmrp interface.

usdDvmrpS32PrunesOnly.name: usdDvmrpS32PrunesOnly
usdDvmrpS32PrunesOnly.description: Identifies when Dvmrp is sending prunes and grafts with only a 32 bit source masks.

usdDvmrpAclDistNbrTable.name: usdDvmrpAclDistNbrTable
usdDvmrpAclDistNbrTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the access lists distance for a list of neighbors.

usdDvmrpAclDistNbrEntry.name: usdDvmrpAclDistNbrEntry
usdDvmrpAclDistNbrEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the usdDvmrpAclDistNbrTable.

usdDvmrpAclDistNbrIfIndex.name: usdDvmrpAclDistNbrIfIndex
usdDvmrpAclDistNbrIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which DVMRP is enabled.

usdDvmrpAclDistNbrAclListName.name: usdDvmrpAclDistNbrAclListName
usdDvmrpAclDistNbrAclListName.description: The name of the access list to be used in the filter

usdDvmrpAclDistNbrDistance.name: usdDvmrpAclDistNbrDistance
usdDvmrpAclDistNbrDistance.description: The administritive distance metric that will be used

usdDvmrpAclDistNbrNbrListName.name: usdDvmrpAclDistNbrNbrListName
usdDvmrpAclDistNbrNbrListName.description: This is the access list of nbrs for this accept-filter to be applied, this field must be supplied when the row is created

usdDvmrpLocalAddrTable.name: usdDvmrpLocalAddrTable
usdDvmrpLocalAddrTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the local addresses. This is used to retrive all of the addresses configured on a DVMRP interface.

usdDvmrpLocalAddrTableEntry.name: usdDvmrpLocalAddrTableEntry
usdDvmrpLocalAddrTableEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the usdDvmrpLocalAddrTable.

usdDvmrpLocalAddrIfIndex.name: usdDvmrpLocalAddrIfIndex
usdDvmrpLocalAddrIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which DVMRP is enabled.

usdDvmrpLocalAddrAddrOrIfIndex.name: usdDvmrpLocalAddrAddrOrIfIndex
usdDvmrpLocalAddrAddrOrIfIndex.description: For unnumbered interfaces, this takes on the value of the ifIndex. For numbered interfaces, this is the address of one of the addresses associated with the interface.

usdDvmrpLocalAddrMask.name: usdDvmrpLocalAddrMask
usdDvmrpLocalAddrMask.description: The Ip Address mask associated with this entry.

usdDvmrpSummaryAddrTable.name: usdDvmrpSummaryAddrTable
usdDvmrpSummaryAddrTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the DVMRP summary addresses. This is used to retrive all of the summary address configured on a DVMRP interface.

usdDvmrpSummaryAddrTableEntry.name: usdDvmrpSummaryAddrTableEntry
usdDvmrpSummaryAddrTableEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the usdDvmrpSummaryAddrTable.

usdDvmrpSummaryAddrIfIndex.name: usdDvmrpSummaryAddrIfIndex
usdDvmrpSummaryAddrIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which DVMRP is enabled.

usdDvmrpSummaryAddrAddress.name: usdDvmrpSummaryAddrAddress
usdDvmrpSummaryAddrAddress.description: This is the summary address that will be created

usdDvmrpSummaryAddrMask.name: usdDvmrpSummaryAddrMask
usdDvmrpSummaryAddrMask.description: The mask of the summary address to be created

usdDvmrpSummaryAddrCost.name: usdDvmrpSummaryAddrCost
usdDvmrpSummaryAddrCost.description: The administritive distance metric used to actually calculate distance vectors.

usdDvmrpInterfaceTable.name: usdDvmrpInterfaceTable
usdDvmrpInterfaceTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the router's multicast-capable interfaces. This table augments the DvmrpInterfaceTable.

usdDvmrpInterfaceEntry.name: usdDvmrpInterfaceEntry
usdDvmrpInterfaceEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the usdDvmrpInterfaceTable. This row extends ipMRouteInterfaceEntry in the IP Multicast MIB, where the threshold object resides.

usdDvmrpInterfaceAutoSummary.name: usdDvmrpInterfaceAutoSummary
usdDvmrpInterfaceAutoSummary.description: Enables or disable auto-summarization on this interface.

usdDvmrpInterfaceMetricOffsetOut.name: usdDvmrpInterfaceMetricOffsetOut
usdDvmrpInterfaceMetricOffsetOut.description: The distance metric for this interface which is used to calculate outbound distance vectors.

usdDvmrpInterfaceMetricOffsetIn.name: usdDvmrpInterfaceMetricOffsetIn
usdDvmrpInterfaceMetricOffsetIn.description: The distance metric for this interface which is used to calculate inbound distance vectors.

usdDvmrpInterfaceAdminState.name: usdDvmrpInterfaceAdminState
usdDvmrpInterfaceAdminState.description: Controls whether DVMRP is enabled or not.

usdDvmrpPruneTable.name: usdDvmrpPruneTable
usdDvmrpPruneTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the router's upstream prune state.

usdDvmrpPruneEntry.name: usdDvmrpPruneEntry
usdDvmrpPruneEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the usdDvmrpPruneTable.

usdDvmrpPruneGroup.name: usdDvmrpPruneGroup
usdDvmrpPruneGroup.description: The group address which has been pruned.

usdDvmrpPruneSource.name: usdDvmrpPruneSource
usdDvmrpPruneSource.description: The address of the source or source network which has been pruned.

usdDvmrpPruneSourceMask.name: usdDvmrpPruneSourceMask
usdDvmrpPruneSourceMask.description: The address of the source or source network which has been pruned. The mask must either be all 1's, or else usdDvmrpPruneSource and usdDvmrpPruneSourceMask must match usdDvmrpRouteSource and usdDvmrpRouteSourceMask for some entry in the usdDvmrpRouteTable.

usdDvmrpPruneIIFIfIndex.name: usdDvmrpPruneIIFIfIndex
usdDvmrpPruneIIFIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the upstream interface for this source group entry.

usdDvmrpPruneUpTime.name: usdDvmrpPruneUpTime
usdDvmrpPruneUpTime.description: This is the amount of time that this prune has remained valid

usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifTable.name: usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifTable
usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifTable.description: The (conceptual) OIFs for particular source group entries.

usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifEntry.name: usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifEntry
usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifTable.

usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifGroup.name: usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifGroup
usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifGroup.description: The group address which has been pruned

usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifSource.name: usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifSource
usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifSource.description: The address of the source or source network which has been pruned

usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifSourceMask.name: usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifSourceMask
usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifSourceMask.description: The address of the source or source network which has been pruned. The mask must either be all 1's, or else usdDvmrpPruneSource and usdDvmrpPruneSourceMask must match usdDvmrpRouteSource and usdDvmrpRouteSourceMask for some entry in the usdDvmrpRouteTable.

usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifOIFIfIndex.name: usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifOIFIfIndex
usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifOIFIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of one of the downstream interfaces for this source group entry.

usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifOIFPruned.name: usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifOIFPruned
usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifOIFPruned.description: If true this oif has been pruned

usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifOIFDnTTL.name: usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifOIFDnTTL
usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifOIFDnTTL.description: The timeout for this OIF. If usdDvmrpSrcGrpOifOIFPruned is false then this is undefined.

usdDvmrpRouteHogNotificationTrap.name: usdDvmrpRouteHogNotificationTrap
usdDvmrpRouteHogNotificationTrap.description: This is an indication that the route hog notification limit has been exceeded during the past minute. It may mean that a route surge is going on.

usdDvmrpCompliance.name: usdDvmrpCompliance
usdDvmrpCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Unisphere DVMRP MIB.

usdDvmrpBaseGroup.name: usdDvmrpBaseGroup
usdDvmrpBaseGroup.description: A collection of objects providing basic management of DVMRP in a Unisphere product.

usdDvmrpAclDistNbrGroup.name: usdDvmrpAclDistNbrGroup
usdDvmrpAclDistNbrGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management of DVMRP access list distance neighbors in a Unisphere product.

usdDvmrpInterfaceGroup.name: usdDvmrpInterfaceGroup
usdDvmrpInterfaceGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management of a DVMRP interface in a Unisphere product.

usdDvmrpSourceGroup.name: usdDvmrpSourceGroup
usdDvmrpSourceGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management of a DVMRP source group in a Unisphere product.

usdDvmrpNotificationGroup.name: usdDvmrpNotificationGroup
usdDvmrpNotificationGroup.description: A notification for signaling important DVMRP events.
